4. Manufacturing Production Monitoring System
Develop a Java program to monitor daily production in a manufacturing company 
using Class and Objects.
Data Members:
• Product ID 
• Product Name 
• Target Quantity 
• Produced Quantity 
Methods:
1. Read product details. 
2. Compare actual production with the target. 
3. Calculate production efficiency percentage. 
4. Display production status (Achieved/Not Achieved). 
Note: Efficiency = (Produced Quantity / Target Quantity) × 100.
import java.util.Scanner;

class Production {
    int pid, targetQty, producedQty;
    String pname;
    double efficiency;

    void read() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.print("Product ID: ");
        pid = sc.nextInt();
        sc.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Product Name: ");
        pname = sc.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Target Quantity: ");
        targetQty = sc.nextInt();

        System.out.print("Produced Quantity: ");
        producedQty = sc.nextInt();
    }

    void calculate() {
        efficiency = (double) producedQty / targetQty * 100;
    }

    void display() {
        System.out.println("\nEfficiency = " + efficiency + "%");

        if (producedQty >= targetQty)
            System.out.println("Status: Achieved");
        else
            System.out.println("Status: Not Achieved");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Production p = new Production();
        p.read();
        p.calculate();
        p.display();
    }
}
Output
Product ID: 1
Product Name: Pen
Target Quantity: 1000
Produced Quantity: 900

Efficiency = 90.0%
Status: Not Achieved
5. Online Course Enrollment System
Develop a Java program for an online learning platform using Class and Objects.
Data Members:
• Student ID 
• Student Name 
• Course Name 
• Course Fee 
Methods:
1. Read student and course details. 
2. Calculate the payable amount. 
3. Provide a 15% scholarship discount if the fee exceeds ₹20,000. 
4. Display enrollment and payment details. 
Note: Registration fee = ₹500.
import java.util.Scanner;

class CourseEnrollment {
    int sid;
    String sname, course;
    double fee, total;

    void read() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.print("Student ID: ");
        sid = sc.nextInt();
        sc.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Student Name: ");
        sname = sc.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Course Name: ");
        course = sc.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Course Fee: ");
        fee = sc.nextDouble();
    }

    void calculate() {
        total = fee + 500;

        if (fee > 20000)
            total = total - (total * 0.15);
    }

    void display() {
        System.out.println("\nEnrollment Details");
        System.out.println("Student Name: " + sname);
        System.out.println("Total Amount = Rs." + total);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        CourseEnrollment c = new CourseEnrollment();
        c.read();
        c.calculate();
        c.display();
    }
}
